Kent.White River Valley Museum:
White River Valley Museum is a historical museum located in Auburn, Washington.


== History ==
Created through the combined effort of the City of Auburn and the White River Valley Historical Society, the White River Valley Museum has been open to the public as far back as January 1996. Since then, the museum has published a monthly newsletter, "White River Journal", while working to preserve regional historical artifacts and sites, including the Mary Olsen Farm.
